Working of ARP:
4 minute video -> https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pPUzAXQFVyQ
5 minute video -> https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1jncvd6JDoc

When a MAC address is unknown, an ARP request is sent which is a BROADCAST address whereas an ARP reply is always a UNICAST message
since the MAC address of the device sending the message is known to the destination machine which sends the ARP reply.
Hence, ARP reply is always UNICAST
